To simplify \(\frac{9^2 - 4^2}{9 - 4}\), factor the numerator as a difference of squares:

9² – 4² = (9 – 4)(9 + 4).

So the expression becomes
\[
\frac{(9 - 4)(9 + 4)}{9 - 4}
\;=\;
9 + 4
\;=\;
13.
\]

To divide by a fraction, multiply by its reciprocal:

\[
-\,\frac34\div\frac{x}{3}
=-\frac34\;\times\;\frac{3}{x}
=-\frac{3\cdot3}{4\cdot x}
=-\frac{9}{4x}\,.
\]
